## Outputs

- `finetune/{model-slug}/prepare.py` — data prep + format conversion.
- `finetune/{model-slug}/config.yaml` (or `train.py`) — recipe.
- `finetune/{model-slug}/data/{train,val,test}.jsonl` + `SHA256SUMS`.
- `finetune/{model-slug}/evals/` — paired before+after eval via
  `/eval-harness`.
- `finetune/{model-slug}/RECIPE.md` — full recipe.

---

## Edge cases

- **Catastrophic forgetting:** small-data fine-tunes drop general capability.
  Add a regularization eval (subset of MMLU or HumanEval) that catches
  drift. Flag in RECIPE.md.
- **Mode collapse on DPO:** DPO with `beta` too high produces repetitive
  outputs. Default `beta=0.1`, eval includes a diversity metric (distinct-n).
- **Quantization loss after merge:** LoRA-merged models lose some quality
  on 4-bit serving. Recommend GPTQ / AWQ over naive bnb-4bit for
  production.
- **Multi-node training:** out of scope. Skill flags and points to
  DeepSpeed Zero-3 / FSDP docs.
- **Closed-source base model:** OpenAI / Anthropic fine-tuning APIs use a
  different shape. Skill detects and emits the API-specific recipe instead.
- **License-incompatible base model:** refuse to scaffold a commercial
  project unless user acknowledges with `--license-ack`.

